<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[212,1172,647,774]" box="[212,344,647,671]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
<heading box="[212,344,647,671]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,344,647,671]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[212,1172,647,774]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
Native to America, Amazon Basin (
<collectingCountry box="[619,690,686,710]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[701,756,687,710]" name="Peru" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[768,850,686,710]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Cowie RH &amp; Thiengo SC" box="[872,1156,686,710]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="41 - 100" refId="ref9716" refString="Cowie RH, Thiengo SC. 2003. The apple snails of the Americas (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Asolene, Felipponea, Marisa, Pomacea, Pomella): a nomenclatural and type catalog. Malacologia. 45: 41 - 100." type="journal article" year="2003">Cowie and Thiengo 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[247,310,718,742]" name="Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Chile</collectingCountry>
, this species was found for the first time in the country in 2000 (
<bibRefCitation author="Letelier S &amp; Ramos AM &amp; Huaquin L" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="9 - 13" refId="ref11852" refString="Letelier S, Ramos AM, Huaquin L. 2007. Moluscos dulceacuicolas exoticos en Chile. Rev Mex Biodivers. 78: 9 - 13." type="journal article" year="2007">Letelier et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and has been recorded only in Santiago (
<geoCoordinate box="[817,912,750,774]" degrees="33" direction="south" minutes="27" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" precision="925" value="-33.45">
33°27 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[882,888,750,774]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[927,1035,750,774]" degrees="70" direction="west" minutes="38" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" precision="925" value="-70.63333">
70°38 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[990,996,750,774]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[212,771,846,910]" box="[212,682,846,870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
<heading box="[212,682,846,870]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,682,846,870]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Possible mechanism of introduction/Status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[212,771,846,910]" box="[212,771,886,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
Aquarium trade/established (
<bibRefCitation author="Letelier S &amp; Ramos AM &amp; Huaquin L" box="[541,755,886,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="9 - 13" refId="ref11852" refString="Letelier S, Ramos AM, Huaquin L. 2007. Moluscos dulceacuicolas exoticos en Chile. Rev Mex Biodivers. 78: 9 - 13." type="journal article" year="2007">Letelier et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[212,1171,982,1077]" box="[212,310,982,1006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
<heading box="[212,310,982,1006]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,310,982,1006]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[212,1171,982,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
Polyphagous, invasive, they can compete with native freshwater species (
<bibRefCitation author="Aditya G &amp; Raut SK" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="919 - 921" refId="ref8528" refString="Aditya G, Raut SK. 2001. Food of the snail, Pomacea bridgesii, introduced in India. Curr Sci. 80: 919 - 921." type="journal article" year="2001">Aditya and Raut 2001</bibRefCitation>
). EA, I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
